Songs in this album have something in common. It's Friday, so what the heck...

1) Catchy tone

2) Everybody has heard them before

3) Make no mistake, this ain't Pink Floyd, Leonard Cohen or John Lennon stuff.  They're more like, well, Duran Duran or Bee Gees.

4) We normally don't want to expose on last.fm the fact that we sometimes listen to them, albeit secretly.

p.s. I was never a big fan of Dancing Queen or YMCA

